info.description:
## üßë‚Äçü§ù‚Äçüßë Demographics & GeoEnrichment API

**The requests on this collection use the environment variables**. If you haven't followed the steps in the "**How to set your free API key üîë** " section in the [Postman ArcGIS Location Service workspace](https://www.postman.com/arcgis-developer/workspace/) now is a good time to do it üòú.

NOTE: If you have an ArcGIS Developer account, you will need to enable Pay-as-you-go to access the service.

## üìÑ Guides and API reference

*   GeoEnrichment API: [Guide](https://developers.arcgis.com/documentation/mapping-apis-and-services/demographics/services/geoenrichment-service/)
*   [REST API parameters](https://developers.arcgis.com/rest/geoenrichment/api-reference/geoenrichment-service-overview.htm)
    

## üõ†Ô∏è Integration

Libraries and wrappers to access this API:

*   Backend: [Node.js](https://developers.arcgis.com/arcgis-rest-js/demographic-data/query-demographic-data/) and [Python](https://developers.arcgis.com/python/guide/performing-geoenrichment/).

urlencoded.description: (Required) You need a valid access token. To learn more, read the collection's documentation.
(Required) The format of the data returned. The value can be json, csv, or geojson.
(Required) An array of input points, polygons, administrative boundaries, or addresses.

(Required) You need a valid access token. To learn more, read the collection's documentation.
(Required) The format of the data returned. The value can be json, pjson (formatted), or html (not supported by all requests).
(Required) An array of input points, polygons, administrative boundaries, or addresses.
An array of data collection names to query for. The names contain pre-defined set of attributes to return for the world or different countries.

urlencoded.description: (Required) You need a valid access token. To learn more, read the collection's documentation.
(Required) The format of the data returned. The value can be json, pjson (formatted), or html (not supported by all requests).
(Required) An array of input points, polygons, administrative boundaries, or addresses.

An array of values to control how input points are buffered. Supported area types include ring buffers and network service areas such as drive times and walk times. Multiple buffer radii can be requested. The unit of measurement requested can be miles or kilometers and in the case of service areas, minutes and hours are also supported.
An array of data collection names to query for. The names contain pre-defined set of attributes to return for the world or different countries.

An optional parameter to request an area's geometry for display on a map. When this parameter is set to true, the geometries of each feature will be included in the repsonse. The default value is false.

item.name: Total households and median households income for the current year (within 5min drive time)
Travel Spending (2021 Airline Fares) around 1 mile radius -117.1042,32.7671 (4218 Biona Pl, San Diego)

request.description:
The Travel Spending data collection (TravelCEX) includes expenditures on travel including airfare, ground transportation, hotels, entertainment and meals on trips.  Consumer Spending data are derived from the 2017 and 2018 Consumer Expenditure Surveys, Bureau of Labor Statistics. Data is reported by product or service and includes total expenditures, average spending per household, and a Spending Potential Index (SPI).  This collection contains data from Esri's 2021 Consumer Spending database

2021 Airline Fares (X7003_X)

Habits¬Æ is a database that contains a full description of the Spanish population and its precise geographical location. This information provides a wide range of possibilities in developing marketing and sales strategies, vastly improving decision-making in many areas.

Habits¬Æ segments the Spanish families typologies based on their demographic and economic characteristics, offering a large amount of economic indicators of Spanish households as income, expenses and property value.

Habits¬Æ can know the presence and expenses profile of each type of household in each geographic micro area of Spain, facilitating precise calculation of the business opportunities in the territory. Habits¬Æ also enables information to be assigned to your own databases for enrichment and segmentation.

Habits¬Æ variables are built on public databases, mostly provided by the INE1. All data used are suitably anonymised and therefore comply scrupulously the LOPD. request.description:
The GeoEnrichment service provides a helper method that returns standard geography IDs and features for the supported geographic levels.

The most common workflow for this service is to find a FIPS (standard geography ID) for a geographic name. For example, you can use this service to find the FIPS for the county of San Diego which is 06073. You can then use this FIPS ID within the GeoEnrichment service study area definition to get geometry and optional demographic data for the county. This study area definition is passed as a parameter to the GeoEnrichment service to return data defined in the enrichment pack and optionally return geometry for the feature.

---|---|---
